  "market_context": "Gold weekly chart showed a fair value gap below and a prior swing high that was swept by up-close candles, followed by a close back below those highs, creating a weekly bearish order block as a higher time frame point of interest.",
  "key_observation": "When price on the 4-hour rallied into the weekly order block and swept a local swing high, the up-close candles in that sweep formed a lower-time-frame order block; this cascade repeated multiple times, each new order block supporting price lower toward standard deviation targets.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the weekly chart identify the existing fair value gap below and the swing high above as context.",
    "Step 2: Mark the up-close candles that swept the weekly swing high and failed to close above as a weekly bearish order block (point of interest).",
    "Step 3: Drop to the 4-hour timeframe and wait for price to rally up into that weekly order block area (still below the weekly FVG).",
    "Step 4: Watch for a lower-timeframe sweep of a 4H swing high just below the POI, followed by an aggressive close below the up-close candles and ideally below the prior low, defining a 4H order block and market structure shift.",
    "Step 5: Apply standard deviation projections from the manipulation leg (high to low), targeting the -2 to -2.5 and -4 to -4.5 areas.",
    "Step 6: Price reaches the first standard deviation, retraces back to the 4H order block; bodies respect it and price continues lower.",
    "Step 7: On the retracement, a new lower-time-frame sweep of a high with up-close candles and close below creates another nested order block and another MSS, allowing fresh projections.",
    "Step 8: Observe that overlapping standard deviation zones from successive projections cluster as confluence targets; price continues to cascade lower, hitting each successive order block and projection level."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price respected each newly formed order block as resistance and delivered lower through multiple standard deviation targets (first SD, then into the overlapping second SD zone, then to a new low), validating the cascade.",
  "lessons": "After higher-timeframe POIs are reached, lower-timeframe up-close candles that sweep highs and close back below become actionable order blocks. Stacking these with standard deviation projections from each manipulation leg produces repeatable bearish continuation setups with clear targets.",
